        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 7:53PM EDT by NWS Columbia SC</headline>
        <description>At 753 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Gaston, or 11 miles south of Cayce, moving north at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
West Columbia, Cayce, Oak Grove, South Congaree, Pine Ridge, Gaston,
SC State Farmer's Market, Columbia Metro Airport, Sandy Run, Swansea,
New Zion, Lexington Acres Pond, Peachtree Rock, Silver Lake, and
Dixiana.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 26 between mile markers 112 and 127.
Interstate 77 between mile markers 0 and 4.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
